.TH "CanvasRenderingContext2D.closePath" "JS" "July 26, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
CanvasRenderingContext2D.closePath \- CanvasRenderingContext2D:
closePath() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]CanvasRenderingContext2D.closePath()\f[B]\f[R] method of
the Canvas 2D API attempts to add a straight line from the current point
to the start of the current sub\-path.
If the shape has already been closed or has only one point, this
function does nothing.
.PP
This method doesn\[cq]t draw anything to the canvas directly.
You can render the path using the \f[CR]stroke()\f[R] or
\f[CR]fill()\f[R] methods.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
closePath()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Closing a triangle
This example creates the first two (diagonal) sides of a triangle using
the \f[CR]lineTo()\f[R] method.
After that, the triangle\[cq]s base is created with the
\f[CR]closePath()\f[R] method, which automatically connects the
shape\[cq]s first and last points.
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]canvas\f[R] id=\[dq]canvas\[dq]></\f[B]canvas\f[R]>
.EE
.SS JavaScript
The triangle\[cq]s corners are at (20, 140), (120, 10), and (220, 140).
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] canvas = document.getElementById(\[dq]canvas\[dq]);
\f[B]const\f[R] ctx = canvas.getContext(\[dq]2d\[dq]);

ctx.beginPath();
ctx.moveTo(20, 140); \f[I]// Move pen to bottom\-left corner\f[R]
ctx.lineTo(120, 10); \f[I]// Line to top corner\f[R]
ctx.lineTo(220, 140); \f[I]// Line to bottom\-right corner\f[R]
ctx.closePath(); \f[I]// Line to bottom\-left corner\f[R]
ctx.stroke();
.EE
.SS Result
.SS Closing just one sub\-path
This example draws a smiley face consisting of three disconnected
sub\-paths.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] Although \f[CR]closePath()\f[R] is called after all the
arcs have been created, only the last arc (sub\-path) gets closed.
.RE
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]canvas\f[R] id=\[dq]canvas\[dq]></\f[B]canvas\f[R]>
.EE
.SS JavaScript
The first two arcs create the face\[cq]s eyes.
The last arc creates the mouth.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] canvas = document.getElementById(\[dq]canvas\[dq]);
\f[B]const\f[R] ctx = canvas.getContext(\[dq]2d\[dq]);

ctx.beginPath();
ctx.arc(240, 20, 40, 0, Math.PI);
ctx.moveTo(100, 20);
ctx.arc(60, 20, 40, 0, Math.PI);
ctx.moveTo(215, 80);
ctx.arc(150, 80, 65, 0, Math.PI);
ctx.closePath();
ctx.lineWidth = 6;
ctx.stroke();
.EE
